column1: Annual taxable retail sales in nominal dollars by county (see previous page for cities)
Annual Sales and Use Tax Reports

Taxable sales measure the reported sales of goods and services that are subject to the statewide retail sales tax.  Because many retail transactions are exempt or otherwise excluded from the state sales tax, the values reported here do not capture all retail activity occurring within a given locality.
Annual totals for FY2009 and later reflect a fiscal year beginning on July 1st.  Annual totals prior to FY2009 reflect a fiscal year beginning on April 1st.
This table reports current, or nominal dollar values.  In order to compare sales over time, users should adjust the values for inflation using the Consumer Price Index (CPI) or a similar measure.
